   <topic>GMT Function</topic>
 <description>GMT() returns Greenwich Mean Time on the system clock as a Formatted_Short_Time ('HH:MM:SS'). For information on the optional Format_String parameter.
 </description>   
   <syntax>Formatted_Short_Time as C = GMT([C time_format])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>time_format</name>
         <description>Optional. Default = "hh:mm:ss". The format for the time value. Character</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
  
   <sections>
       <section><title>Example</title>
            <description>put description here</description>
            <example><![CDATA[gmt() -> "19:31:18"]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
